Content: [Shut down blahhhhhhhhhh](https://preview.redd.it/3okkpnsn13uf1.png?width=1555&format=png&auto=webp&s=91735765a17540d4a88e7c9f373a573254275c02)

I'm so fucking over this shutdown like always.  This is stupid.  Both sides are stupid.  Shutdowns used to be a random thing and now they are the norm which is just another sign of our broken political system.  But yea this is old.  Get ready for a monster relief rally if we get a shutdown compromise.  It will power this entire thing higher for sure.

Yesterday NVDA powered the rest of the tech market higher and AMD finally had the green day that you guys have been screaming about.  That is what a positive day looks like.  That is a day where we closed higher than the open which means that the pre-market push wasn't sold off.  Again, crazy that I have to explain how candlestick charting works to all of these "experts" who are coming for me in the comments but yea.  Someone also pointed out that this thread has turned into a Macro conversation thread with little AMD analysis.  So I would love to take a stab at that:

Technical analysis is about finding a trend and then trading or making investments off of that trend.  Use statistical probabilities with a variety of studies that make predictions based on historical averages, human psyche, algorithmic trading parameters, expected price movement, etc.  When there is a giant NEWS DRIVEN EVENT, that trend is broken.  So I can't really comment specifically in real time on every single detail about AMD bc we are in a whole new world.  Gonna take a little bit for everything to sort itself out and for us to get a new data set and establish a new trend.  

We were all trading a trend for the past 2 months when AMD broke sideways out of our up channel bc that was a trend.  That trend is broken so we need to let the chart calm down.  That is one of the draw backs of technical analysis.  It can't work  24/7 and it can't account for news driven events.  So you do end up sittin
